Name: CVE-2020-6577
Description: The IT-Recht Kanzlei plugin in Zen Cart 1.5.6c (German edition) allows itrk-api.php rechtstext_language SQL Injection.
References: MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/usd-2019-0072/

Name: CVE-2020-6578
Description: Zen Cart 1.5.6d allows reflected XSS via the main_page parameter to includes/templates/template_default/common/tpl_main_page.php or includes/templates/responsive_classic/common/tpl_main_page.php.
References: MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/usd-2019-0069/

Name: CVE-2020-6579
Description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in mailhive/cloudbeez/cloudloader.php and mailhive/cloudbeez/cloudloader_core.php in the MailBeez plugin for ZenCart before 3.9.22 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the cloudloader_mode parameter.
References: MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/usd-2019-0070/

Name: CVE-2020-6581
Description: Nagios NRPE 3.2.1 has Insufficient Filtering because, for example, nasty_metachars interprets \n as the character \ and the character n (not as the \n newline sequence). This can cause command injection.
References: FEDORA:FEDORA-2020-d436ed655f   |   URL:https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/2DNGKXVDB43E3KQRA6W5QZT3Z46XZLQM/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/usd-2020-0002/

Name: CVE-2020-6582
Description: Nagios NRPE 3.2.1 has a Heap-Based Buffer Overflow, as demonstrated by interpretation of a small negative number as a large positive number during a bzero call.
References: FEDORA:FEDORA-2020-d436ed655f   |   URL:https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/2DNGKXVDB43E3KQRA6W5QZT3Z46XZLQM/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/   |   MISC:https://herolab.usd.de/security-advisories/usd-2020-0001/

Name: CVE-2020-6583
Description: BigProf Online Invoicing System (OIS) through 2.6 has XSS that can be leveraged for session hijacking. An attacker can exploit the XSS vulnerability, retrieve the session cookie from the administrator login, and take over the administrator account via the Name field in an Add New Client action.
References: MISC:https://www.sevenlayers.com/index.php/282-online-invoicing-system-2-6-xss-session-hijack

Name: CVE-2020-6584
Description: Nagios Log Server 2.1.3 has Incorrect Access Control.
References: MISC:https://assets.nagios.com/downloads/nagios-log-server/CHANGES.TXT   |   MISC:https://medium.com/@fixitt6/multiple-vulnerabilities-in-nagios-log-server-2-1-3-af7c160edc60   |   MISC:https://www.nagios.com/products/nagios-log-server/

Name: CVE-2020-6585
Description: Nagios Log Server 2.1.3 has CSRF.
References: MISC:https://assets.nagios.com/downloads/nagios-log-server/CHANGES.TXT   |   MISC:https://medium.com/@fixitt6/multiple-vulnerabilities-in-nagios-log-server-2-1-3-af7c160edc60   |   MISC:https://www.nagios.com/products/nagios-log-server/

Name: CVE-2020-6586
Description: Nagios Log Server 2.1.3 allows XSS by visiting /profile and entering a crafted name field that is mishandled on the /admin/users page. Any malicious user with limited access can store an XSS payload in his Name. When any admin views this, the XSS is triggered.
References: MISC:https://assets.nagios.com/downloads/nagios-log-server/CHANGES.TXT   |   MISC:https://medium.com/@fixitt6/multiple-vulnerabilities-in-nagios-log-server-2-1-3-af7c160edc60   |   MISC:https://www.nagios.com/products/nagios-log-server/
